### What happened?

On previous versions of our Grafana Cloud instance, these Stat labels were easily readable. However, since this week, we have noticed the font size to be much smaller than before. See the following screenshot (ignore the error messages of other visualizations)

<img width="586" height="145" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/374e2a9f-b259-4ff8-9a33-abe547f14599" />

### What did you expect to happen?

The text should appear like this (screenshot from a couple of weeks ago)

<img width="515" height="142" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ec4926c0-2f53-4646-a311-1519b7dfb252" />

### Did this work before?

Yes, on a previous version of Grafana Cloud the text was much bigger (and more legible). Unfortunately, I don't know the previous Grafana version as I am using Grafana Cloud. A week ago it looked fine.

### How do we reproduce it?

1. Create a Stat with the string "84:96:90:77:63:92" as the content and resize it


